  <summary date="2019-01-30T05:00:00Z" status="Introduced in House">Expanded Stalking Protections Act of 2019

This bill broadens the scope of conduct that constitutes a federal stalking offense.

Specifically, it expands stalking to include conduct that causes a person's friend or co-worker to experience a reasonable fear of death or serious bodily injury.</summary>
